<subSubSection pageNumber="817" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="817">
Croat (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="817">Ann. Missouri Bot. Gard.</emphasis>
63: 504. 1977) indicated either 514.1 or 514.2 (LINN) as type but, as noted by Wijnands (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="817">Bot. Commelins</emphasis>
: 185. 1983), neither is original material for the name. Although Wijnands suggested that Clifford material (BM) might be an appropriate choice as type, he did not do this formally and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Penningtonâ€™s">Pennington's</normalizedToken>
choice therefore has priority.
</paragraph>
